FIPS: Taxable sales measure the reported sales of goods and services that are subject to the statewide retail sales tax.  Because many retail transactions are exempt or otherwise excluded from the state sales tax, the values reported here do not capture all retail activity occurring within a given locality.
Annual totals for FY2009 and later reflect a fiscal year beginning on July 1st.  Annual totals prior to FY2009 reflect a fiscal year beginning on April 1st.
"NA" indicates that retail data were not published for a given city in that year
This table reports current, or nominal dollar values.  In order to compare sales over time, users should adjust the values for inflation using the Consumer Price Index (CPI) or a similar measure.
